@node NTC_Info "NTC Info"

   NTC-resistors are cheep and can be found in every electronic store.

   NTC-resistors have a very temperature dependent resistance.
   NTC = Negative Temperature Coefficient = lower resistance at higher 
   temperatures.

   NTC-resistors consists of chrome, manganese, iron, cobalt and nickel.

   R = A * e^(B / T) there 

   R = Resistance in ohm
   T = Temperature in Kelvin = Degree Celsius + 273.15
   A = Material constant
   B = Material constant
   
   R25 = Resistance at 25 degree Centigrade.

   @{" Data for R25 =  10k " link Data10000}
   @{" Data for R25 = 100k " link Data100000}
   @{" Data for R25 = 220k " link Data220000}
   @{" Data for R25 = 330k " link Data330000}

@endnode   

@node NTC_Calibrate "NTC Calibrate"

   There are no default calibration data for NTC-resistors.

   The 'Equ' should be set to '1-deg Exp' or '2-deg Exp'.
   
@endnode

@node NTC_Connection "NTC Connection

Joystick port:   
   
   Connect the NTC-resistors between +5V (Pin 7) and PotX (Pin 5) or
   PotY (Pin 9).
   
   Ex:
   
          PotX (5)--------- wire ------
                                      |
                                     | | NTC #1
Joystick                              |
port #2                ---- wire ------               
          +5V  (7)-----I                  
                       ---- wire ------
                                      |
                                     | | NTC #2
                                      |
          PotY (9)--------- wire ------ 

@endnode


